com.amazonaws.auth.policy.conditions
Class S3ConditionFactory

java.lang.Object
  com.amazonaws.auth.policy.conditions.S3ConditionFactory

public class S3ConditionFactory
extends Object

Factory for creating access control policy conditions specific to Amazon S3. This class provides access to the AWS access control policy condition keys specific to Amazon S3, as well as methods for quickly creating common S3 specific policy conditions such as newCannedACLCondition(CannedAccessControlList).

Method Detail

newCannedACLCondition

public static Condition newCannedACLCondition(CannedAccessControlList cannedAcl)
Constructs a new access policy condition that compares an Amazon S3 canned ACL with the canned ACL specified by an incoming request.

You can use this condition to ensure that any objects uploaded to an Amazon S3 bucket have a specific canned ACL set.

Parameters:
cannedAcl - The Amazon S3 canned ACL to compare against.
Returns:
A new access control policy condition that compares the Amazon S3 canned ACL specified in incoming requests against the value specified.
